 in order to be able to measure it outside of it.
 We position a 10 cm plano-convex lens at a distance of 10 cm directly in
 front of the laser, with its planar side facing the incoming beam.
 Then we place another 10 cm plano-convex lens at a distance of 20 cm away
 from the first lens, now with the convex side facing the incoming beam.
 We adjust the setup slightly so that the beam size, calculated using the
 procedure described in section 2.3.2 with 
\begin_inset Formula $a=1.8\,mm$
\end_inset

