 After finding these two parameters, we extend the laser beam as much as
 possible using mirrors and measure 
\begin_inset Formula $D$
\end_inset

 as a function of 
\begin_inset Formula $z$
\end_inset

, and fit for 
\begin_inset Formula $\Theta$
\end_inset

 by using the previously measured values of 
\begin_inset Formula $D_{0}$
